President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 5 through May 11, 2019, as National Hurricane Preparedness Week. The proclamation encourages Americans living in hurricane-prone areas to take necessary measures to safeguard their families, homes, and businesses. The proclamation highlights the destructive force of hurricanes and the importance of preparing for the upcoming hurricane season. It also emphasizes the dangers of storm surges and the need for timely and reliable forecasts. The proclamation mentions the efforts of the National Weather Service (NWS) to improve storm tracking and intensity predictions. It also emphasizes the administration's commitment to enhancing weather forecasting models and investing in mitigation actions. The proclamation calls upon individuals and emergency management officials to utilize online resources provided by the NWS and FEMA to prepare for hurricanes and severe storms.